cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new technique for training Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) with arbitrarily expressive inference models. It also establishes a connection between VAEs and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are both popular topics in the field of machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as VAEs and GANs are both used in various AI applications such as image and speech generation. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as VAEs and GANs are commonly used in image and video processing tasks. 

It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the use of neural networks in the proposed technique. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the use of a discriminative network to improve the expressiveness of the inference model in VAEs.
